  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the charcoal grill or spit to medium-high heat (around 180°C).",
    "Season the lamb shoulder with cumin, smoked paprika, turmeric powder, salt, and black pepper.",
    "Heat the olive oil in a pan and sauté the garlic and onion until softened.",
    "Rub the lamb shoulder with the garlic and onion mixture, making sure it's evenly coated.",
    "Place the lamb shoulder on the grill or spit, and close the lid.",
    "Smoke the lamb for 2 hours, or until it reaches an internal temperature of 70°C.",
    "Remove the lamb from the heat and let it rest for 10 minutes.",
    "Slice the lamb into thin pieces and serve hot with your choice of sides."
